        <updateDate>2015-05-12T16:52:37Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Housing Financial Literacy Act of 2015 </b></p> <p> Amends the National Housing Act to revise the single insurance premium payment for a mortgage (secured by a one- to four-family dwelling that is an obligation of the Mutual Mortgage Insurance Fund) of a first-time homebuyer who completes a program of counseling on the responsibilities and financial management involved in homeownership that is approved by the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development.</p> <p>Repeals the current maximum premium payment of 2.75% of the amount of the mortgage's original insured principal obligation.</p> <p>Sets the single mortgage insurance premium payment at 25 basis points lower than the premium payment amount otherwise established.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
